  "title": "Digital Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<p>Job Description:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Create and curate engaging and relevant content for various digital platforms, including websites, blogs, social media, and email campaigns.</li>\n  <li>Optimize website content, structure, and keywords to improve search engine rankings and organic visibility.</li>\n  <li>Plan and manage paid advertising campaigns on platforms like Google Ads, Bing Ads, and social media.</li>\n  <li>Manage social media profiles, post content, engage with followers, and analyze performance metrics.</li>\n  <li>Use tools like Google Analytics to track website traffic, user behavior, and engagement metrics.</li>\n  <li>Engage with customers through online platforms, responding to inquiries, comments, and messages.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least Degree in marketing, business, communications, or a related field</li>\n  <li>Proven work experience in marketing, ideally in a marketing executive role</li>\n  <li>Excellent written and verbal communication skills to effectively convey marketing strategies and build relationships with stakeholders</li>\n  <li>Capability to create and implement comprehensive marketing strategies across different channels</li>\n  <li>Understanding of digital marketing tools and platforms like social media, SEO, and email marketing</li>\n  <li>Strong ability to collaborate with different departments and build relationships with clients and partners</li>\n</ul>",
